        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 1:32PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 131 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Kouts to near Lake Village to 6 miles east
of Hopkins Park. Movement was east northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Localized wind gusts up to 50 mph, with localized half inch
hail possible in and near DeMotte.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wheatfield, Kouts, Thayer, Sumava Resorts, Roselawn, Stoutsburg,
DeMotte, Morocco, Schneider, Dunns Bridge, Hebron, Shelby, Lake
Village, and Lowell.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building. Frequent
cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
